# Domain Ownership Rule

**app.inthecircle.co must be attached only to one Vercel project** (production: **inthecircle-web-v2**). If another project has this domain, visitors see that project's app.

## Do

- Before adding or changing domains, run `VERCEL_PROJECT_NAME=inthecircle-web-v2 npm run verify-domain` (requires VERCEL_TOKEN or `vercel login`).
- **Production deploys** happen by pushing to **`main`** (Git-based). Do not run `vercel deploy --prod` for normal releases.
- If adding a domain in Vercel, add it only to **inthecircle-web-v2**; never add app.inthecircle.co to another project.

## If domain is on the wrong project

Run `VERCEL_PROJECT_NAME=inthecircle-web-v2 ./scripts/move-domain-to-inthecircle-web.sh` (requires VERCEL_TOKEN), or in Vercel Dashboard remove app.inthecircle.co from the other project and ensure it is on inthecircle-web-v2.

## See

- `DEPLOYMENT.md` — "Rule: one domain, one project" and Git-based deployment.
- `scripts/verify-domain-ownership.mjs` — verification script.
- `docs/GIT_VERCEL_MIGRATION.md` — migration to Git-based production.
